{"query": {"pages": {"4767411": {"lastrevid": 630148116, "pageid": 4767411, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Boorman", "title": "Scott Boorman", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Scott_Boorman&action=edit", "length": 2230, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-03-30T12:13:44Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Boorman", "revisions": [{"*": "<p><b>Scott Archer Boorman</b> (born February 1, 1949) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematical_sociology\" title=\"Mathematical sociology\">mathematical sociologist</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Yale_University\" title=\"Yale University\">Yale University</a>. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scott_Boorman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He earned his B.A. in Applied Mathematics from <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University\" title=\"Harvard University\">Harvard University</a>, and was a Harvard Junior Fellow. He  received his Ph.D. in <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology\" title=\"Sociology\">Sociology</a> from Harvard University and was appointed to a full professorship at Penn before moving to Yale. He is also a graduate of <a href=\"/wiki/Yale_Law_School\" title=\"Yale Law School\">Yale Law School</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scott_Boorman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>While still a teenager, Boorman wrote <i>The Protracted Game&#160;: A Wei-Ch'i Interpretation of Maoist Revolutionary Strategy</i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://senseis.xmp.net/?TheProtractedGame\">[1]</a> (1969), an analysis of the U.S. involvement in Vietnam. He shows that the U.S. thought it was playing <a href=\"/wiki/Chess\" title=\"Chess\">Chess</a>, while in fact the game was Wei-Ch'i (also known as <a href=\"/wiki/Go_(board_game)\" title=\"Go (board game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Go</a>).\n</p><p>He systematically explores the similarity between the military strategies of Chinese Communist insurgency and the Chinese board game wei-ch\u2019i, in contrast to parallel U.S. analyses of the same events. Boorman also argues that wei-chi's analysis of a strategic system presents a more sophisticated and flexible form of <a href=\"/wiki/Game_theory\" title=\"Game theory\">game theory</a> than the traditional western models of strategic choice.\n</p><p>His book, <i>Genetics of Altruism</i> (1980) uses mathematical population genetics to analyze the development of sociality and altruism through three modes of selection: group, kin and reciprocity.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scott_Boorman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.yale.edu/sociology/faculty/pages/boorman/\">Faculty website at Yale</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.yale.edu/sociology/faculty/pages/boorman/vitaScottBoorman.pdf\">List of publication</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.zonaeuropa.com/20050605_1.htm\">http://www.zonaeuropa.com/20050605_1.htm</a> -(Quotes a <a href=\"/wiki/James_Pinkerton\" title=\"James Pinkerton\">James Pinkerton</a> editorial invoking <i>The Protracted Game</i>)</li></ul>\n<table class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0\"><tr><td style=\"padding:2px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\"><a href=\"/wiki/Authority_control\" title=\"Authority control\">Authority control</a></th><td class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/wiki/Virtual_International_Authority_File\" title=\"Virtual International Authority File\">VIAF</a>: <span class=\"uid\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://viaf.org/viaf/33284808\">33284808</a></span></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Name_Identifier\" title=\"International Standard Name Identifier\">ISNI</a>: <span class=\"uid\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://isni-url.oclc.nl/isni/0000000115655059\">0000 0001 1565 5059</a></span></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>\n<table id=\"persondata\" class=\"persondata noprint\" style=\"border:1px solid #aaa; display:none; speak:none;\">\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"> <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Persondata\" title=\"Wikipedia:Persondata\">Persondata</a>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Name\n</td>\n<td> Boorman, Scott\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Alternative names\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Short description\n</td>\n<td> American sociologist\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Date of birth\n</td>\n<td> February 1, 1949\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Place of birth\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Date of death\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"persondata-label\" style=\"color:#aaa;\"> Place of death\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></table>\n<p><br 